This PR extends the `workspace.protectedFiles` configuration by blocking programmatic read access via `workspace.fs.readFile`.

If a file is marked with `"read": false`, extension-initiated file reads will throw an error.

Example:

```
JSON
"workspace.protectedFiles": {
  "**/.env": {
    "read": false
  }
}
```

Plain string `question.message` values can contain markdown (e.g. `**bold**`, `[link](...)`), but `getQuestionText` returned them as-is, exposing raw markdown syntax to screen readers via `aria-label` attributes and accessibility alerts.

## Changes

- **`getQuestionText`**: Wrap plain strings in `MarkdownString` before calling `renderAsPlaintext`, so all accessibility surfaces (title `aria-label`, container `aria-label`, screen reader alert) receive stripped plain text

```typescript
// Before
private getQuestionText(questionText: string | IMarkdownString): string {
    if (typeof questionText === 'string') {
        return questionText; // raw markdown exposed to screen readers
    }
    return renderAsPlaintext(questionText);
}

// After
private getQuestionText(questionText: string | IMarkdownString): string {
    const md = typeof questionText === 'string' ? new MarkdownString(questionText) : questionText;
    return renderAsPlaintext(md);
}
```

